init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Your body initially begins to break down and liquefy.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The flesh starts peeling off of your bones and the blood begins to run backwards through your body, until you finally melt into a puddle.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It's like having a death sentence on you and not being able to do anything about it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The scientists were only able to test the drug for a few hours and they believed that it was going to be safe forever.
